      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/77/10",
      "text": [
        " «إِذَا كَانَ عَلَى وَجْهِ اَلْجَهَالَةِ أَعَادَ اَلْحَجَّ وَ عَلَيْهِ بَدَنَةٌ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2844 - Ali ibn Abi Hamza narrated from Imam Abu al-Hasan (as):\nHe was asked about a man who forgot to perform the circumambulation around the Kaaba (Tawaf) until he returned to his family.\nImam (as) replied: \"If it was out of ignorance, he must repeat the Hajj and offer a sacrifice of a camel.\""
        ]
      }
